# Plans vs feature records

## Where to look

| Need | Read |
|------|------|
| Current behavior, invariants, routes, code map | [`docs/features/README.md`](../../docs/features/README.md) |
| **New `chimera-*` wrapper or supervised binary** | [Wrapper binary contract](../../docs/features/chimera-wrapper-binary-contract.md), [Product naming](../../docs/features/product-naming-contract.md), [Structured log lines](../../docs/features/structured-operator-log-lines.md) |
| **Chat routing, tool router, fallback, or new router stage** | [Gateway chat routing pipeline](../../docs/features/gateway-chat-routing-pipeline.md) |
| Future intent or draft design | [`docs/plans/`](../../docs/plans/) with `Status: draft` or `active` |
| Delivery history, phase acceptance, rationale | Shipped plans in [`docs/plans/README.md`](../../docs/plans/README.md) |
| Install, run, configure | [`docs/README.md`](../../docs/README.md) operator runbooks |
| Product vision + normative requirements | [`docs/chimera.plan.md`](../../docs/chimera.plan.md) |
| Integration references (BiFrost, token notes) | [`docs/reference/`](../../docs/reference/) |

## Rules for agents

1. **Do not implement from a shipped plan** if a feature record exists — the feature record is behavioral source of truth.
2. **Draft plans may not match the codebase** — verify in code before assuming behavior exists.
3. **After shipping behavior**, update or create the feature record; add an **As-built** link in the plan front-matter table.
4. **Platform contracts** (`Doc kind: platform-contract`) describe extender/binary integration — read before adding wrappers or normalizers.
5. **Operator features** (`Doc kind: feature-record`) describe UI and operator-visible product behavior.
6. **Do not delete shipped plans** — they preserve delivery context; feature records distill what must stay true going forward.

## When changing operator or indexer behavior

1. Read the relevant feature record(s) first.
2. Change code and tests.
3. Update the feature record if invariants, interfaces, or code map changed.
4. Link new work to a draft plan if one exists; mark the plan shipped when done.

## When adding a new wrapped binary

1. Read [chimera-wrapper-binary-contract.md](../../docs/features/chimera-wrapper-binary-contract.md).
2. Implement `wrapper/runtime.Adapter` and use `internal/naming` env keys.
3. Add a `*line` normalizer for structured stderr; follow [structured-operator-log-lines.md](../../docs/features/structured-operator-log-lines.md).
4. Add e2e contract tests mirroring broker/vectorstore patterns.
5. Update feature record if the shared contract changes; extend pipeline doc **Target extensibility** when adding a stage.

## When adding a chat router stage (transform, retrieval, policy, admission)

1. Read [gateway-chat-routing-pipeline.md](../../docs/features/gateway-chat-routing-pipeline.md) for stage order and invariants.
2. Prefer extending an existing stage package (`transform`, `rag`, `routing`, `providerlimits`, `chat`) before new orchestration in handlers.
3. Wire config through virtual model stack where operator-visible; document new fields in [operator-virtual-models.md](../../docs/features/operator-virtual-models.md) if settings change.
4. Add stable log slugs to [operator message registry](../../docs/features/operator-log-message-registry.md).
5. Do not call upstream outside `chat.WithVirtualModelFallback` unless explicitly designing a new stage type documented in the pipeline feature.
